<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-11-18T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-11-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="358" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3578: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-11-18T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            18, 1921—12 noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>299. Your telegram No. 406, November 17. See telegraphic instructions
                                297, November 17, 5 p.m.<note n="88" xml:id="d358fn88"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_384">p.
                                    384</ref>.</note> You are confidentially informed that reliable
                                information has reached the Department that the Chinese Government
                                has been advised by its Minister here that the payment of its loans
                                without any more delay is extremely urgent.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>